{"author":{"id":"5e53c9bce7eeb69e347743575f6133426338c29498e200aa8bf1bef46209d02a"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1635346968,"nonce":"LdyqEbVGsV/dw4tdTwuPfU6cxXs=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOAW4Y0s4914GF","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/4119","origin":"github"},"title":"medaka_consensus_pipeline still writes to input dirs","message":"@pavanvidem updated this tool to symlink its fasta input to fix this in #3941 but unfortunately, [the too canonicalizes the input path](https://github.com/nanoporetech/medaka/blob/afe3607a3f8c7a95fc4c7bda9df10e1f0bbff717/scripts/medaka_consensus#L50):\n\n```bash\nfunction follow_link {\n  python -c 'import os,sys; print(os.path.realpath(sys.argv[1]))' $1\n}\n\n# ...\n\nwhile getopts ':hi::d:o:gm:ft:b:' option; do\n  case \"$option\" in\n    h  ) echo \"$usage\" \u003e\u00262; exit;;\n    i  ) iflag=true; BASECALLS=$(follow_link $OPTARG);;\n    # ...\n  esac\ndone\n```\n\nThe only way around this short of modifying medaka is going to be to copy the input, but that can be very expensive. I don't know what input sizes are like for this tool.","files":null}]}